The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Corporate Briefs

 Savita Chemicals Ltd will issue bonus shares in the ratio of 2:3. The board at its meeting decided to issue bonus shares by capitalisation of permitted reserves in the ratio of two bonus shares for every three equity shares held by the shareholders, the company informed the Bombay Stock Exchange. The board also re-appointed C.V. Alexander, who is also the secretary of the company, as its whole-time director from October 1 to September 30, 2007. 

 Punj Lloyd has received an order of $290 million from Libyas Sirte Oil Company to build pipelines projects on engineering, procurement and construction basis. The order comprises two contracts. The first is a construction of a 98.4-km pipeline from Tripoli to Melita and a 21-km branch pipeline to Zawia power plant; the second involves completion of a 157-km pipeline from El Khoms to Tripoli.

 Ess Dee Aluminium Ltd has filed its draft red herring prospectus with the Securities and Exchange Board of India for its proposed initial public offering. The company proposes to offer 69.6 lakh shares of Rs 10 each for cash at premium to be decided through 100 per cent book building.

 Fitch Ratings has assigned AA(ind) national long-term debt rating to UTI Banks Rs 215-crore perpetual Tier I and Rs 653-crore unsecured Tier II capital issues. The agency has also affirmed AA+(ind) national long-term rating to the banks Rs 2,500-crore subordinated debt programme. 

